cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The use of feedback and power constraints suggests a possible sub-category of cs.SI (signal processing). The mention of power control and expected power constraints also suggests a possible sub-category of cs.MM (multimedia). The use of multiple access channels suggests a possible sub-category of cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). Finally, the use of asymptotic expansions and bounds suggests a possible sub-category of cs.LG (machine learning).
